abstract: General Electric delivered a solid gain in first-quarter earnings despite lower demand for industrial equipment.
snippet: General Electric delivered a solid gain in first-quarter earnings despite lower demand for industrial equipment.
lead_paragraph: General Electric delivered a solid gain in first-quarter earnings on Friday despite economic weakness, especially in Europe, which is holding back demand for industrial equipment.

headline.main: G.E. Reports a 16% Rise in Quarterly Profit
